The niProtocol Firefox extension enables Firefox to access an ni: link using a .well-known URL
as described in RFC 6920 [http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6920].

The extension gets the <authority> (domain name) from the parent page URL and converts 
ni:///sha-256;<hash> to
http://<authority>/.well-known/ni/sha-256/<hash>

To try it in Firefox, download
https://github.com/jefft0/nuvl/raw/master/ni-protocol/firefox/ni-protocol.xpi
In Firefox, open Tools > Add-ons. In the "gear" or "wrench" menu, click Install Add-on From File 
and open niProtocol.xpi. Restart Firefox.

More information and demos are at http://nuvl.org/ni
